---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Project Portfolio | Belvedere Decks"
  description="Recent composite deck projects in Montgomery County, MD — before-and-after transformations and the framing photos most builders never show you."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Portfolio</p>
      <h1>The work, documented honestly.</h1>
      <div class="rule"></div>
      <p class="lead">
        Every project we build is photographed at three moments: before, at framing
        inspection, and finished. Most builders only show you the third one.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Why we photograph the framing</h2>
      <p>
        The framing photo is the one that matters. It shows the joist spacing, the
        flashing at the house, the connectors with every fastener hole filled, and the
        footings that passed county inspection — the parts of your deck you'll never see
        again once the boards go down. We post ours because we're proud of them.
      </p>

      <!-- GALLERY: populate with real project photos only.
           Per content policy: no stock images, no placeholder projects, no AI-generated
           hero shots. Each entry needs: before shot, framing shot, finished hero,
           town, service line, board/rail spec. First entries: Hammil (Boyds),
           Bonaparte — when built and photographed. -->
      <div class="notice">
        <strong>Current projects are under construction.</strong> Finished galleries land
        here as each build completes — before-and-after pairs, the framing shots, and the
        specifications, project by project. Check back soon, or
        <a href="/contact">ask to see work in progress</a>.
      </div>

      <p><a class="btn primary" href="/contact">Talk about your project</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
